-- Aena to Cut 66% of Workforce in Small Airports, Cinco Dias Says
-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 2012-07-14T12:21:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-14/aena-to-cut-66-of-workforce-in-small-airports-cinco-dias-says.html
Aena Desarrollo Internacional SA, a
Spanish airport operator, plans to cut the workforce at its 17
smallest airports and two smallest heliports by 66 percent,
 Cinco Dias  reported, citing an announcement made by the company
to the unions yesterday.  The reductions are part of a plan to reduce operating
hours, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  